Python Control Flow :
Title: Iterating Through a List Using Index and Value

Concept:
To access both the index and the element of a list at the same time, Python provides the built-in enumerate() function.
It returns pairs of (index, value) for each item in the iterable.

Tech used :
Language : pyhton
Compiler : Visual Studio Code

Logic Flow:
enumerate(lst) generates a sequence of (index, value) tuples.
In the for loop, both index and value can be unpacked directly.
You can also convert the enumerate object to a list using list(enumerate(lst)) for display.
